<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870824-0019 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Tosco Corp.</HL><DD> 08/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TOSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Michael E. Tennenbaum, a Los Angeles-based managing director of Bear, Stearns andamp; Co., said he holds the equivalent of a 6.87% stake in the common shares outstanding of Tosco Corp., a Santa, Monica, Calif.-based independent refiner.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mr. Tennenbaum said he holds 2,335,542 Tosco common shares, assuming the conversion of $4 million principal amount of 4% notes and some Series E preferred stock that he holds. He said in the filing that his stake is for investment purposes, and that he may buy more Tosco securities or sell some of his holdings in the future.    A Tosco spokesman said that Mr. Tennnenbaum was elected a Tosco director in June and that the company had no reason to doubt that his holding is for investment purposes only. </TEXT></DOC>